A legislation to adopt a common name to be spelt as EGBIRA for all Ebira ethnic groups in Kogi, Edo and Nassarawa States. This legislation was completed and contained in the Federal Republic of Nigeria's Official Gazette No. 127, Volume 109, dated July 14, 2022. By this official gazette, the name EGBIRA is henceforth the officially recognized name for Ebira people in Kogi, Edo and Nassarawa States.
